{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-1-chapter-level-1-tsx","path":"/topics/feverish-children-risk-assessment/supporting-evidence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"4b445d56-0770-5401-be3f-4ff8bf9ab5a7","slug":"supporting-evidence","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","depth":1,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field b467ee21-cf18-435a-9a01-92a4fe788e3c --><h1>Supporting evidence</h1><!-- end field b467ee21-cf18-435a-9a01-92a4fe788e3c -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item d096b2b0-58c3-47a8-b1be-eb9868cbb4d1 --><!-- begin field ae534b59-a677-4792-a028-a99d00c1d6b6 --><p>This CKS topic is largely based on the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) clinical guidelines <em>Feverish illness in children: assessment and initial management in children younger than 5 years</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/feverish-children-risk-assessment/references/\">NICE, 2017</a>] and <em>Urinary tract infection in children: diagnosis, treatment and long-term management</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/feverish-children-risk-assessment/references/\">NICE, 2018</a>], a US emergency medicine policy document <em>Clinical policy for well-appearing infants and children younger than 2 years of age presenting to the emergency department with fever</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/feverish-children-risk-assessment/references/\">Mace, 2016</a>], the Resuscitation Council (UK) guideline <em>Paediatric basic life support</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/feverish-children-risk-assessment/references/\">Resuscitation Council (UK), 2015</a>], a Task Force Report of the International League Against Epilepsy (ILAE) Commission of Pediatrics <em>Summary of recommendations for the management of infantile seizures</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/feverish-children-risk-assessment/references/\">Wilmshurst, 2015</a>], a Cochrane systematic review <em>Prophylactic drug management for febrile seizures in children</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/feverish-children-risk-assessment/references/\">Offringa, 2017</a>], and expert opinion in review articles. The rationale for the individual recommendations is discussed in the relevant basis for recommendation sections.</p><!-- end field ae534b59-a677-4792-a028-a99d00c1d6b6 --><!-- end item d096b2b0-58c3-47a8-b1be-eb9868cbb4d1 -->","topic":{"id":"860d5be6-8e34-52f3-8489-8e036e18e0ee","topicId":"d4cc7c3b-fd82-4173-98d1-6f6028c90872","topicName":"Feverish children - risk assessment","slug":"feverish-children-risk-assessment","lastRevised":"Last revised in July 2020","chapters":[{"id":"a7225e98-6779-5db2-bd32-b85e54b565f6","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"d279dbca-6eb3-58cc-8866-d501504746c1","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"4c8bb62e-af88-52a7-a1b1-ace4c3bbde4b","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"befd0a68-876b-5c0c-954f-c8c0cd45075f","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"2ae43109-4ced-5043-953b-8ab3cff8bef1","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"5223b6f6-55ff-52a2-889a-359063c588a0","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"70d4d24b-0bf7-5f39-a648-f618feb078c6","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"d0d52e49-9e81-5dab-817e-b785b8d0044e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"0d544b0e-4f7d-5987-b908-e72d8fe7a207","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"46b15a11-b7a5-56b3-9bc5-6a77f72a0f4d","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"7fc386b9-863d-5963-bb61-7172b92d8852","slug":"qipp-opt